[EHD is the most important disease of white-tailed deer. Outbreaks are common in many USA states, but there are no previous records in the western location reported here.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of the affected area can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/8OW_. - Mod.PMB

A great photo of a white-tailed deer showing its tail in all it's glory is at: http://www.thesportsglobe.com/Wildlife/Images/whitetail_deer_02.jpg
- Mod.JW]
